Modern Ecology

Maryse Biernat

December 5, 2016

Modern Ecology

Question/Hypothesis

Are there significant relationships between abiotic factors, such as precipitation and temperature, and the functional characteristics of mammalian communities?

Datasets

Lintulaakso and Kovarovic 2016

Bioclim variables from WorldClim

Functional Traits

Browser

Grazer

Mixed Feeder

Frugivore

Insectivore

Terrestrial

Terrestrial-aquatic

Bioclim

Mean Annual Temperature

Mean Annual Precipitation

Temperature Seasonality

Precipitation Seasonality

Code

library(dplyr)
library(raster)
library(ggplot2)
library(rgdal)
library(rgeos)

theme_set(theme_bw(20))
census <- src_sqlite("~/census.db")
occurrence <- tbl(census, "occurrence")
taxon <- tbl(census, "taxonomy")
modern.loc  <- tbl(census, "censusLocation")
fun_traits <- tbl(census, "functional_traits")
Modern.census <- left_join(occurrence, taxon, by = c("taxon_id" = "id"))%>%
  filter(ref_id.x == 13) %>%
  left_join(modern.loc, by = c("location_id" = "id")) %>%
  left_join(fun_traits, by = c("taxon_id" = "taxon_id")) %>%
  dplyr::select(abundance, family, tribe, genus, species, country, shortName, latitude, longitude, mmAveragePrecipitation, locomotor_reed, trophic_lintulaakso) %>% #
  group_by(country, shortName, genus, species) %>%
  collect()
percents <- group_by(Modern.census, shortName) %>%
  mutate(perGrazers = sum(trophic_lintulaakso=="G") / n(), perBrowsers = sum(trophic_lintulaakso=="B") / n(), perMixedFeeders = sum(trophic_lintulaakso=="MF") / n(), perPiscivores = sum(trophic_lintulaakso=="P") / n(), perFrugivores = sum(trophic_lintulaakso== c("FG","FH","FO")) / n(), perInsectivores = sum(trophic_lintulaakso==c("I", "IO","M")) / n(), perArboreal = sum(locomotor_reed=="A") / n(), perArbTer = sum(locomotor_reed=="AT") / n(), perSubTer = sum(locomotor_reed=="ST") / n(), perTerrestrial = sum(locomotor_reed=="T") / n(), perTerAquatic = sum(locomotor_reed=="TA") / n()) %>%
  summarise(latitude = unique(latitude), longitude = unique(longitude), perGrazers = unique(perGrazers), perBrowsers = unique(perBrowsers), perMixedFeeders = unique(perMixedFeeders), perPiscivores = unique(perPiscivores), perFrugivores = unique(perFrugivores), perInsectivores = unique(perInsectivores), perArboreal = unique(perArboreal), perArbTer = unique(perArbTer), perSubTer = unique(perSubTer), perTerrestrial = unique(perTerrestrial), perTerAquatic = unique(perTerAquatic)) %>%
  collect()
Bioclim <- getData(name="worldclim", var="bio", res = 2.5)
plot(Bioclim$bio1, main= "World Mean Annual Temperature")

africa <- readOGR("C:\\Users\\beach\\Documents\\Fall2016.Paleo.Research\\Africaoutline\\africa_simple.shp", "africa_simple")
## OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile 
## Source: "C:\Users\beach\Documents\Fall2016.Paleo.Research\Africaoutline\africa_simple.shp", layer: "africa_simple"
## with 1 features
## It has 3 fields
bio1 <- projectRaster(Bioclim$bio1, crs = proj4string(africa), res = c(10000, 10000))
maskafrica.bio1 <- mask(bio1, africa)
maskafrica.bio1 <- crop(maskafrica.bio1, extent(africa))
plot(maskafrica.bio1, main="Mean Annual Temperature")

bio12 <- projectRaster(Bioclim$bio12, crs = proj4string(africa), res = c(10000, 10000))
maskafrica.bio12 <- mask(bio12, africa)
maskafrica.bio12 <- crop(maskafrica.bio12, extent(africa))
bio4 <- projectRaster(Bioclim$bio4, crs = proj4string(africa), res = c(10000, 10000))
maskafrica.bio4 <- mask(bio4, africa)
maskafrica.bio4 <- crop(maskafrica.bio4, extent(africa))
bio15 <- projectRaster(Bioclim$bio15, crs = proj4string(africa), res = c(10000, 10000))
maskafrica.bio15 <- mask(bio15, africa)
maskafrica.bio15 <- crop(maskafrica.bio15, extent(africa))
SP <- SpatialPoints(cbind(percents$longitude, percents$latitude), proj4string = CRS("+init=epsg:4326"))
SP <- spTransform(SP,proj4string(africa))
siteIndicesinAfrica <- which(!is.na(over(SP, africa)[,1]))
SP <- SP[siteIndicesinAfrica]
percents <- dplyr::select(percents, -latitude, -longitude)
percents <- percents[siteIndicesinAfrica,]
class(percents) <- "data.frame"
SPDataframe <- SpatialPointsDataFrame(SP, percents)
plot(maskafrica.bio1, main="Mean Annual Temperature")
plot(SPDataframe, add=T, pch=16)

SPDataframe@data$MeanAnnualTemp <- extract(bio1, SPDataframe)
plot(maskafrica.bio4, main="Temperature Seasonality")
plot(SPDataframe, add=T, pch=16)

SPDataframe@data$TempSeasonality <- extract(bio4, SPDataframe)
plot(maskafrica.bio12, main="Annual Precipitation")
plot(SPDataframe, add=T, pch=16)

SPDataframe@data$AnnualPrecip <- extract(bio12, SPDataframe)
plot(maskafrica.bio15, main="Precipitation Seasonality")
plot(SPDataframe, add=T, pch=16)

SPDataframe@data$PrecipSeasonality <- extract(bio15, SPDataframe)
